  "informal_statement": "Define isEven, isOdd : ℕ → Bool by mutual recursion (isEven 0 = true, isEven (k+1) = isOdd k; isOdd 0 = false, isOdd (k+1) = isEven k). Every natural number n is classified as even or odd: isEven n = true or isOdd n = true.",
  "informal_proof_idea": "Induction on n. Base case: isEven 0 = true by definition. Successor case: unfold one mutual-recursion step (isEven (k+1) = isOdd k, isOdd (k+1) = isEven k) and apply the inductive hypothesis, which is exactly the same disjunction for k with the two disjuncts swapped.",
  "formal_statement_pp": "theorem even_odd_mutual_totality (n : ℕ) : isEven n = true ∨ isOdd n = true",
